All Classes

  • Class Description
    AuthToken
    This object associates a token with a user, allowing the user to authenticate requests to the server with the token after logging in instead of a password.
    AuthTokenDAO
    Allows saving and verifying AuthTokens stored in the database.
    ClearResponse
    Response returned to handler from ClearService if service is successful.
    ClearService
    Deletes ALL data from the database, including user accounts, auth tokens, and generated person and event data.
    DAO
    This class is the parent of the object-specific DAO classes.
    ErrorResponse
    Response that is returned to handler if an error occurs while processing service.
    Event
    Object that stores information about a particular event linked to a person.
    Event.EVENT_TYPES
    An enum that stores the types of events that this object can represent.
    EventDAO
    Allows the saving and retrieving of event information from the database.
    EventIDResponse
    Response returned to handler from EventIDService if service is successful.
    EventIDService
    Returns the single Event object with the specified ID.
    EventResponse
    Response returned to handler from EventService if service is successful.
    EventService
    Returns ALL events for ALL family members of the current user.
    FillResponse
    Response returned to handler from FillService if service is successful.
    FillService
    Populates the server's database with generated data for the specified user name.
    LoadRequest
    Request object that handler passes to LoadRequest containing information to load.
    LoadRequestUser
    Object containing user information.
    LoadResponse
    Response returned to handler from LoadService if service is successful.
    LoadService
    Clears all data from the database (just like the /clear API), and then loads the posted user, person, and event data into the database.
    LoginRequest
    Request object that handler passes to LoginService containing authentication information.
    LoginResponse
    Response returned to handler from LoginService if service is successful.
    LoginService
    Logs in the user and returns an auth token.
    Person
    Object storing biological information about a person in the map system.
    PersonDAO
    Allows the saving and retrieving of Person objects from the database.
    PersonIDResponse
    Response returned to handler from PersonIDService if service is successful.
    PersonIDService
    Returns the single Person object with the specified ID.
    PersonResponse
    Response returned to handler from PersonService if service is successful.
    PersonService
    Returns ALL family members of the current user.
    RegisterRequest
    Request object that handler passes to RegisterService containing information about new user.
    RegisterResponse
    Response returned to handler from RegisterService if service is successful.
    RegisterService
    Creates a new user account, generates 4 generations of ancestor data for the new user, logs the user in, and returns an auth token.
    ServiceException
    Exception thrown by Service classes if an error occurs performing service.
    User
    Object that stores user information, like login details.
    UserDAO
    Allows saving and retrieving Users from the database.
